<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=200&amp;p=26190#p26190"><![CDATA[
Look up, way up to top of Classic Shell page. Look in the &quot;Home&quot; tab,<br />or here is direct link to old 3.6.8 install package: <br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/classicshell/files/latest/download?source=files">https://sourceforge.net/projects/classi ... urce=files</a><!-- m --><br /><br />If you don't like uninstalling, reinstalling, I fixed skin to work in CSM 4.2.5<br />There were a couple of separator/pager reference errors,<br />and the search bitmap was out of registration on HDPI. <br />There is the simple quick fix v2.5 2 column only, and the bigger fix v2.6 1 &amp; 2 column for CSM v4.2.5<br /><br />dJuL made it to work in Windows 8. If using in Windows 10, the grey menu might be too bright, or have residual glass blur color on it.<br />To fix, uncheck the &quot;Enable menu glass&quot; in the &quot;menu Look&quot; tab of CSM settings.<br />Glass system color on Win 10 will be stronger on menu. <br /><br />Let me know if something was missed.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Sat Apr 16, 2016 4:54 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
